---
title: Creamy Mushroom Chowder with Couscous with Spinach, Croutons & Lemon
description: This isn’t your mom’s chowder—nope, no seafood here. Instead, it’s loaded with veggies but still creamy as all get out (plus it’s ready in just 15 minutes!). We’re talking about a steaming bowl of herbaceous broth studded with meaty mushrooms, fresh spinach, and scallions. And to beef up the texture, Israeli couscous plays its springy part, as do crunchy croutons. This lunchtime bowl is finished with a bright squeeze of lemon for a veggie chowda even your mom would be prouda!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/649af67ac8e13be2fa91de92-362e4524.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/649af67ac8e13be2fa91de92.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 410 kcal
  fat: 18 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 54 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 11 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1410 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-mushroom-chowder-with-couscous-649af67ac8e13be2fa91de92
cuisine: Italian
time required: 15 minutes
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a medium #pot over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites, mushrooms, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in 2 cups water, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a low simmer. Cook until couscous and veggies are tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, quarter @lemon{1}.

In a small #bowl, combine half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon} with 1 TBSP water (all the cornstarch and 2 TBSP water for 4 servings).

Once couscous and veggies are tender, add @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @Italian herb paste{1%tablespoon}, @spinach{2.5%ounce}, and cornstarch mixture to pot. Stir to combine and cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Divide chowder between bowls; top with @croutons{1} and scallion greens. Serve with a squeeze of lemon juice and remaining lemon wedges on the side.